So US federal R&D spending
on new energy technology

00:38:47.590 --> 00:38:49.660
when we wrote this
piece was about half

00:38:49.660 --> 00:38:55.940
of what it was in actual
dollars because it was in 1980.

00:38:55.940 --> 00:38:58.570
So the blue is public
sector investment.

00:38:58.570 --> 00:39:02.230
You can see the high
watermark about 1980,

00:39:02.230 --> 00:39:04.450
and it's come down since then.

00:39:04.450 --> 00:39:07.120
The gray line is private
sector investment levels.

00:39:07.120 --> 00:39:09.580
You can, again, see
that that's basically

00:39:09.580 --> 00:39:12.220
through this 2005 time
period and it hasn't

00:39:12.220 --> 00:39:15.390
gotten much better since.

00:39:15.390 --> 00:39:17.812
That basically fell in
half, as well, right?

00:39:17.812 --> 00:39:19.270
So this is not the
picture you want

00:39:19.270 --> 00:39:23.290
to have if you're going to
do a technology revolution,

00:39:23.290 --> 00:39:24.250
all right?

