00:55:14.920 --> 00:55:17.006
did over the years.

00:55:17.006 --> 00:55:18.600
I had to understand
those reports

00:55:18.600 --> 00:55:20.700
because I had to help
those communities bring

00:55:20.700 --> 00:55:23.100
their reports to
the policy world,

00:55:23.100 --> 00:55:24.790
so I had to read
in pretty deeply--

00:55:24.790 --> 00:55:30.330
so a lot of what I'm stumbling
onto in the article you read,

00:55:30.330 --> 00:55:33.630
but also the book that is
a larger statement of it

00:55:33.630 --> 00:55:35.940
really comes out of
my MIT experience.

00:55:35.940 --> 00:55:37.680
And of course Sloan
was pretty deeply

00:55:37.680 --> 00:55:41.730
involved in each one of
those, which was part

00:55:41.730 --> 00:55:44.300
of what made them powerful.

00:55:44.300 --> 00:55:47.280
But Martin, when I
do the next edition,

00:55:47.280 --> 00:55:51.160
I'm going to get you to
