01:16:40.060 --> 01:16:44.810
So-- I do think that
these steps here

01:16:44.810 --> 01:16:48.230
are steps that you've got
to think through when you're

01:16:48.230 --> 01:16:49.850
innovating in a legacy sector.

01:16:49.850 --> 01:16:52.230
You've got to think about the
different innovation models

01:16:52.230 --> 01:16:54.843
you've got, and how to
organize those in new ways,

01:16:54.843 --> 01:16:57.260
because all of them are going
to be required in the legacy

01:16:57.260 --> 01:16:59.747
sector-- but you also
have to think about,

01:16:59.747 --> 01:17:01.080
what are your launch categories?

01:17:01.080 --> 01:17:02.360
What are the barriers to launch?

01:17:02.360 --> 01:17:04.235
How are you going to
overcome those barriers?

01:17:04.235 --> 01:17:06.800
What's the right incentive
package and support system?

01:17:06.800 --> 01:17:10.815
Can you do niche launch, which
gets you out of this whole box?

01:17:10.815 --> 01:17:12.690
What are the gaps in
your information system?

01:17:12.690 --> 01:17:15.170
I think you've got to
go through all of those

01:17:15.170 --> 01:17:17.895
when you think about legacy
sector innovation in general,

01:17:17.895 --> 01:17:20.270
and we did a little of that
in the health care discussion

01:17:20.270 --> 01:17:22.348
last week.

